    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Looking for an affordable set of wheels that still has plenty to offer? This car isn\u2019t perfect, but it starts, runs, and gives you a lot of value for someone who wants dependable basic transport, a practical project, or a handy spare vehicle. I believe in being upfront: it shows its age and wear, but it\u2019s priced fairly and could be a great fit for the right buyer. If you want something inexpensive without the big price tag, this one is worth a look.",
      "price": 6950.0,
      "reputation": 0.9,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Well-sorted project car with strong basic fundamentals and plenty of life left for the next owner. Engine fires up eagerly, pulls cleanly through the rev range, and the drivetrain feels mechanically straightforward and serviceable. A good candidate for someone who wants an affordable driver, weekend wrenching project, or solid platform to improve over time. Not a showpiece, but it has honest character, usable road manners, and the kind of old-school mechanical feel enthusiasts appreciate. Priced to move and worth a look if you want something inexpensive with potential.",
      "price": 5800.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
